\(\textbf{probability of an
    outcome} = \dfrac{1}{\textbf{the total number of equally-likely outcomes}}\)

    <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="Body-no-indent">You will now investigate whether
    Archie's theory is correct.</p>

